### Changelog v2 — Layout & Scale Updates

**RouteLayout Compatibility**
- Removed the outer `min-h-screen` wrapper — height is now managed by `RouteLayout`'s `<main className="flex-1">` as intended.
- Added `pt-24` to the page root to create clearance below the fixed NavBar, matching what's visible in your screenshot.

**Typography & Text Scaling**
- Page heading bumped from `text-4xl` → `text-5xl` to match the weight of other pages.
- Body/description text scaled from `text-xs` → `text-sm` across all cards for better readability.
- Section headings (Data Science, Tools & Platforms, Career & Internships Corner) scaled up from `text-lg/xl` → `text-2xl/3xl`.

**Card Sizing**
- Academic cards: padding increased from `p-6` → `p-8`, card titles from `text-base` → `text-xl font-bold`.
- Career cards: padding increased from `p-5` → `p-6`, titles from `text-sm` → `text-base font-bold`.
- Tool icons: wrapper size increased and padding from `py-4` → `py-6` for better presence.
- "Learn More »" links: scaled from `text-xs` → `text-sm font-bold` to match design.

**Spacing & Layout**
- Max width widened from `max-w-5xl` → `max-w-6xl` to use more horizontal space on desktop.
- Section gap increased from `space-y-10` → `space-y-12`, card gaps from `gap-5/6` → `gap-6`.
- Filter tab padding increased to `px-6 py-2.5` for a larger, more clickable feel.
- Tag pills updated to match the outlined style seen in the screenshot (white bg + green border).